[2] Cholera - Tanzania (Mara Region)
Date: Mon 13 Apr 2015
Source: Tanzania Daily News [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504132406.html


2 major markets have been closed indefinitely in Rorya District of Mara Region following an outbreak of cholera in the area. According to the Rorya District Administrative Secretary ((DAS), Mr Daud Murumbe, the closed markets are Utegi and Randa. "Apart from the markets, all small restaurants that were not complying to hygienic regulations were also closed," Mr Murumbe told the 'Daily News'.

"So far, we have 7 cholera patients admitted," the official said, adding that 2 health centers of Utegi and Kowaki have been put on standby to handle cholera patients. The most affected villages include Utegi, Nyanguge and Nyanduga. He said that authorities in Rorya District are doing everything possible to stop further spread of the disease in the area.

"Health officials are also going around the entire district urging people to observe hygiene," the DAS said. Lack of latrines in many homes in Rorya is reportedly making the District prone to frequent cholera outbreaks.

Late last week, Rorya District CCM Chairman, Mr Samwel Keboye called for immediate construction of latrines in all markets scattered in various parts of the District. "Most of the markets have no latrines. This is shameful. All markets must be closed before the situation gets out of hand," the CCM leader said shortly after he visited cholera patients at Utegi health centre where he donated medicines and other items in a bid to improve treatment for patients.

[Byline: Mugini Jacob]

